        <num>CC 714</num>
        <heading>714.  Co-owner; servitude on entire estate</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 714.  Co-owner; servitude on entire estate.
A predial servitude on an estate owned in indivision may be established only with the consent of all the co-owners.
When a co-owner purports to establish a servitude on the entire estate, the contract is not null; but, its execution is suspended until the consent of all co-owners is obtained.</p>
        </content>
